                     and is one of the key polls used for the BCS<fn>Bowl Championship Series</fn>.
                    The voters in the AP poll are a group of sportswriters and broadcasters chosen from across the country. 
                    The top <m>25</m> teams are ranked using a Borda count: each first-place vote is worth <m>25</m> points, 
                    each second-place vote is worth <m>24</m> points, each third-place vote is worth <m>23</m> points, and so on. 
                    The following table shows the ranking and total points for each of the top three teams at the end of 
                    the <m>2006</m> regular season. (The remaining <m>22</m> teams are not shown here because they are irrelevant to this exercise.)
                </p>
                <tabular top="medium" bottom="minor">
                    <row header="yes">
                        <cell halign="left">Team</cell>
                        <cell halign="left">Points</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell halign="left">1. Ohio State</cell>
                        <cell halign="left">1625</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell halign="left">2. Florida</cell>
                        <cell halign="left">1529</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell halign="left">3. Michigan</cell>
                        <cell halign="left">1526</cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </introduction>
            <task>
